OL,3,CLabour MP calls on Reform UK to stop
OL,4,Cboycott of local newspaper
OL,6,F"Those who put themselves forward for
OL,7,Fpublic office have a duty to answer
OL,8,Fquestions, explain the decisions they
OL,9,Ftake and face the democratic scrutiny
OL,10,Fthe public rightly expects, as you
OL,11,Fyourself have twice this week.
OL,13,F"It is especially important for
OL,14,FCouncils to engage with local
OL,15,Fcommunities through their local
OL,16,Fnewspapers, which are often the key
OL,17,Fchannel through which residents learn
OL,18,Fabout decisions that affect their
OL,19,Fdaily lives.
