OL,3,CLabour MP calls on Reform UK to stop
OL,4,Cboycott of local newspaper
OL,6,FIn a statement, Reform UK said: "The
OL,7,FReform Council has always placed the
OL,8,Fprinciples of transparency,
OL,9,Faccountability, and free speech at the
OL,10,Fheart of our work.
OL,12,F"We firmly believe that open dialogue
OL,13,Fis vital to a healthy democracy, and
OL,14,Fwe welcome scrutiny that is conducted
OL,15,Fwith fairness, balance, and integrity.
OL,17,F"However, we also have a duty to
OL,18,Fprotect the credibility of our
OL,19,Fgovernance and the voices of those we
OL,20,Frepresent.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/8
